WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:01.828
First impressions?

00:01.960 --> 00:03.496
Looks like it crushed
the punter's throat,

00:03.629 --> 00:04.789
held a knife to the madame.

00:04.922 --> 00:07.004
She said it was acting angry
just like a human.

00:07.132 --> 00:09.544
I saw the forensics leaving.
What are you trying to hide?

00:11.261 --> 00:13.513
You're suspended from duty,
active immediately.

00:13.639 --> 00:14.503
ANITA: For legal reasons,

00:14.640 --> 00:16.756
a synthetic appliance
cannot self-examine.

00:16.892 --> 00:18.553
My clothes must be removed.

00:18.685 --> 00:21.427
Yeah. I was afraid
you were going to say that.

00:21.563 --> 00:23.770
Would you like me
to open that for you, Peter?

00:23.899 --> 00:26.686
Tell it to stay out of my way!

00:26.818 --> 00:27.728
Pete.

00:27.861 --> 00:30.318
LEO:
You've killed someone, Niska.

00:30.447 --> 00:32.688
And they'll find you.

00:32.824 --> 00:34.030
They'll destroy you.

00:35.160 --> 00:37.321
You can't be allowed to exist.

00:37.454 --> 00:39.536
-AN|TA: Who is Tom?
-LAURA: Shut up!

00:39.665 --> 00:42.327
Never say that name again!
Do you understand?

00:42.459 --> 00:43.824
Promise me!

00:43.961 --> 00:45.952
You're a weirdo, Anita.

00:46.088 --> 00:47.544
I'm going to find out why.

00:47.673 --> 00:49.379
LEO: Oh, my God.

00:49.508 --> 00:51.874
She's here.
We can find her.

00:52.844 --> 00:53.833
I'm here!

00:53.971 --> 00:55.757
Help me! Help me!

00:58.225 --> 01:05.313
We are looking for
a particular group of synths.

01:09.528 --> 01:11.189
SILAS:
This one again.

01:14.074 --> 01:16.531
These Russian junkers
picked her up somewhere.

01:16.660 --> 01:19.777
They brought her to me,
I installed some new software,

01:19.913 --> 01:20.777
and I took my fee.

01:20.914 --> 01:23.030
Where can I find
these Slavic entrepreneurs?

01:23.166 --> 01:25.202
SILAS: I'll tell you exactly
what I told the other bloke.

01:25.335 --> 01:26.495
I've got no idea.

01:26.628 --> 01:27.834
The other bloke?

01:27.963 --> 01:29.794
SILAS:
20s, dark hair,

01:29.923 --> 01:32.335
looked like
he was sleeping rough.

01:32.467 --> 01:36.506
Him and his dolly
were looking for her, too.

01:37.639 --> 01:42.008
His dolly hit my mate.

01:42.144 --> 01:43.759
Properly.

01:43.895 --> 01:46.022
Put him down.

01:46.148 --> 01:48.560
Now, how is that possible?

01:48.692 --> 01:52.059
This other young man,
are you sure he was human?

01:52.195 --> 01:54.481
Oh, you what?

01:54.615 --> 01:56.947
-Was he human?
-S|LAS: Well, he bled.

01:58.493 --> 02:00.950
Blood.

02:11.965 --> 02:14.456
We're not looking
for five synthetics.

02:14.593 --> 02:18.085
We're looking for four
and a human.

02:18.221 --> 02:21.088
There's a young man with them.
Must be protecting them.

02:21.224 --> 02:23.215
I want him to be the focus now,

02:23.352 --> 02:25.809
and those backpacks
we discounted,

02:25.937 --> 02:28.394
I want them tested
for human DNA.

02:28.523 --> 02:31.356
[Theme music playing]

02:40.077 --> 02:42.944
MAN: Could you use some
extra help around the house?

02:45.582 --> 02:47.823
Introducing the world's first
family android.

02:47.959 --> 02:50.792
[ lndistinct talking]

02:51.838 --> 02:53.419
This mechanical maid is capable

02:53.548 --> 02:56.255
of serving more
than just breakfast in bed.

02:57.427 --> 03:00.214
What could you accomplish
if you had someone,

03:00.347 --> 03:02.338
something like this?

03:02.474 --> 03:03.805
[ lndistinct talking]

03:07.729 --> 03:10.641
These machines
will bring us closer together.

03:17.864 --> 03:20.606
[Classical music playing]

03:21.993 --> 03:25.156
Mm, that smells good.

03:25.288 --> 03:29.452
Oh, Pete, don't make a call now.
Breakfast is nearly ready.

03:29.584 --> 03:31.540
[Ringing]

03:31.670 --> 03:32.876
Hello.

03:33.004 --> 03:34.380
PETE:
Hi, Karen, it's me.

03:34.506 --> 03:35.336
Just checking in.

03:35.465 --> 03:36.500
How's gardening leave?

03:36.633 --> 03:37.793
Bored out my mind.

03:37.926 --> 03:41.089
Stuck here until
that little creep from the paper

03:41.221 --> 03:43.587
drops his stupid complaint.

03:43.724 --> 03:45.180
KAREN: Well, there's an argument
that that's what happens

03:45.308 --> 03:47.139
when you assault journalists.

03:47.269 --> 03:48.600
Noted, yeah.

03:48.729 --> 03:50.219
What's happening with the case?

03:50.355 --> 03:52.311
Oh, yeah, solved it.
On to the next thing now.

03:52.441 --> 03:53.305
PETE:
Very funny.

03:53.442 --> 03:56.275
Could you e-mail me over
the case files?

03:56.403 --> 03:59.270
I can't get access
from my home computer.

03:59.406 --> 04:01.192
Oh, yeah, that sounds like
a good idea.

04:01.324 --> 04:03.110
Then we can both be suspended
together.

04:03.243 --> 04:05.609
—J|LL: Pete.
-PETE: I'm on the phone, Jill!

04:05.746 --> 04:08.237
Well, are you going to finish
the call so we can eat together?

04:08.373 --> 04:09.362
I'm not hungry, okay?

04:09.499 --> 04:11.160
Fine.
Well, can you leave, then?

04:11.293 --> 04:13.659
'Cause some of us would like
to have breakfast in peace.

04:13.795 --> 04:15.080
PETE:
Fine. I'm leaving.

04:18.675 --> 04:21.291
Anita?

04:21.428 --> 04:24.215
A word.

04:37.194 --> 04:39.059
How are your systems running?

04:39.196 --> 04:40.777
Fine, thank you, Mattie.

04:40.906 --> 04:42.066
Yeah?

04:42.199 --> 04:45.566
No errors?
Diagnostics all good?

04:45.702 --> 04:47.784
ANITA:
I detect no errors in my system.

04:47.913 --> 04:50.746
l detected a pretty friggin'
big one the other night.

04:50.874 --> 04:52.739
You know, suddenly switching
to kidnap mode.

04:52.876 --> 04:54.582
"I'm here! Help me!"

04:54.711 --> 04:56.622
Remember that?

04:56.755 --> 04:58.461
I'm afraid I don't.

04:58.590 --> 05:00.251
Well, I do.

05:00.383 --> 05:02.715
And it's messed up.
It's weird.

05:02.844 --> 05:05.881
I guess I wanted to make sure
you're okay,

05:06.014 --> 05:08.221
on a mechanical level,
obviously.

05:08.350 --> 05:11.433
My systems are running
at full capacity, Mattie.

05:11.561 --> 05:13.472
Thank you for your concern.

05:13.605 --> 05:15.516
Yeah.

05:15.649 --> 05:18.106
Don't mention it.

05:18.235 --> 05:19.475
Good chat.

05:20.195 --> 05:22.277
Hello, Laura.

05:25.867 --> 05:28.404
You would make a terrible spy.

05:28.537 --> 05:30.778
Whereas you would actually make
a pretty good Bond villain.

05:30.914 --> 05:32.450
What happened to Anita
the other night?

05:32.582 --> 05:33.571
Nothing.

05:33.708 --> 05:36.245
She malfunctioned a bit.

05:36.378 --> 05:38.118
She yelled for help.

05:40.257 --> 05:41.588
Nothing!
Why would you assume I was?

05:41.716 --> 05:45.004
Okay, okay,
don't jump down my throat.

05:46.555 --> 05:47.920
I might have tried to
hack her a little.

05:48.056 --> 05:48.806
Mattie!

05:48.932 --> 05:53.301
But she...she sounded scared.

05:55.522 --> 05:58.810
Synths can't get scared,
can they?

05:59.818 --> 06:01.683
I don't think so.

06:01.820 --> 06:03.356
What would be the point?

06:23.758 --> 06:26.500
[Sighs]

06:29.764 --> 06:31.265
FIONA:
Almost the weekend.

06:31.391 --> 06:33.006
LAURA:
Ugh, don't remind me.

06:33.143 --> 06:35.475
FIONA: Not got anything fun
planned with the kids?

06:35.604 --> 06:37.390
Oh, unless you find
passive aggression

06:37.522 --> 06:38.807
and simmering resentment fun.

06:38.940 --> 06:40.931
I'm a lawyer, aren't I?

06:41.067 --> 06:42.648
Anything good come in?

06:42.777 --> 06:44.859
Not really.
All a bit dry.

06:44.988 --> 06:46.148
Ooh, here's a fun one.

06:46.281 --> 06:48.317
Mrs. Kennedy was thrown
out of a play

06:48.450 --> 06:50.441
for violating
the theater's policy

06:50.577 --> 06:51.987
on synths in the audience.

06:52.120 --> 06:54.736
She's suing
for human rights violations.

06:54.873 --> 06:56.613
Guess whose human rights.

06:56.750 --> 06:58.331
The synth's.

06:58.460 --> 06:59.825
Says her dolly is special.

06:59.961 --> 07:00.950
Special how?

07:01.087 --> 07:03.169
Says he enjoys the plays,
apparently.

07:04.466 --> 07:05.421
Who's taking it?

07:05.550 --> 07:07.381
Don't worry.
We turned her down.

07:07.510 --> 07:10.377
She doesn't need legal aid.
She needs a psychiatrist.

07:22.233 --> 07:26.647
JILL: Pete, can you come in here
a minute?

07:26.780 --> 07:30.523
[Sighs]

07:30.659 --> 07:32.365
I need to talk to you.

07:40.126 --> 07:42.458
What's going on?

07:42.587 --> 07:46.330
I've been thinking...a lot.

07:47.217 --> 07:49.503
And I don't think
you make me happy anymore.

07:49.636 --> 07:54.471
I don't think
that this relationship

07:54.599 --> 07:56.715
is healthy for me anymore,

07:56.851 --> 07:59.809
and I would like
some time apart.

07:59.938 --> 08:03.556
Well, Jill,
I've been suspended from work,

08:03.692 --> 08:06.604
so I literally have to hang
around the house all day.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.772
How can I spend less time
with you?

08:08.905 --> 08:11.897
I don't think it's a good idea
for you to be here right now.

08:12.033 --> 08:13.534
I'm sure
there's places you can go.

08:13.660 --> 08:15.366
[Chuckles]
This is mad.

08:15.495 --> 08:17.577
-|'m sorry.
-PETE: No, don't apologize.

08:17.706 --> 08:20.038
Don't do that.
What's it said to you?

08:20.166 --> 08:21.997
Simon has had nothing to do
with this.

08:22.127 --> 08:23.992
Yes, he --
Yes, it does!

08:24.129 --> 08:26.415
Ever since we got that thing,
this has been coming.

08:26.548 --> 08:28.379
Oh, that's ridiculous!

08:28.508 --> 08:31.341
Jill, I'm a man,
and I'm not perfect.

08:31.469 --> 08:32.629
That's the point.

08:32.762 --> 08:35.720
None of us are.
We're not supposed to be!

08:37.600 --> 08:40.683
-J|LL: Pete, Pete, no!
-Shut up!

08:41.771 --> 08:45.480
Look at me.
Look at me!

08:46.818 --> 08:49.309
Pete, the deposit.

08:49.446 --> 08:50.561
Christ!

09:01.207 --> 09:03.493
Leo, are you trying to steal
a car?

09:03.626 --> 09:05.617
Nope.
Borrow one, if anything.

09:05.754 --> 09:08.791
What do you want me to do, Max?
Carry you to Mia?

09:08.923 --> 09:10.788
We need to find her.

09:10.925 --> 09:13.587
Do you think
Mia will be happy to see us?

09:13.720 --> 09:15.676
Who wouldn't be happy to see us?

09:15.805 --> 09:19.468
Most people we meet nowadays
don't seem to like us very much.

09:19.601 --> 09:22.343
Yeah, well...they just
haven't had a chance

09:22.479 --> 09:23.844
to get to know us yet.

09:23.980 --> 09:25.265
[Click]

09:26.941 --> 09:29.273
The car was unlocked.

09:29.402 --> 09:33.020
Yes, thank you.
I can see that.

09:35.950 --> 09:37.986
The coordinates we have
aren't exact.

09:38.119 --> 09:39.404
No.

09:39.537 --> 09:41.038
So, how are we going to find
the forum user

09:41.164 --> 09:42.779
if we still don't have
their precise location?

09:42.916 --> 09:44.076
Don't worry about that.

09:44.209 --> 09:46.200
I've got a plan
to flush them out.

09:57.138 --> 09:58.253
Hmm?

09:58.389 --> 10:01.096
Wait, Toby.

10:03.561 --> 10:06.223
May I?

10:09.943 --> 10:12.104
Enjoy the party, Toby.

10:12.237 --> 10:14.319
Thank you.

10:22.163 --> 10:24.620
JOE:
They'll be gone for a while.

10:24.749 --> 10:26.364
Sophie's at a sleepover.

10:26.501 --> 10:28.332
Got the place to ourselves.

10:28.461 --> 10:31.077
What do you say we have
a little house party of our own?

10:31.214 --> 10:32.875
[Chuckles]

10:33.007 --> 10:36.215
Actually, I'm going out as well.

10:36.344 --> 10:38.585
Where?

10:38.721 --> 10:41.758
It's a work thing.
Last-minute arrangement.

10:41.891 --> 10:44.007
Who else is going?

10:44.144 --> 10:46.635
No one you know.

10:46.771 --> 10:48.227
I'll see you later.

10:50.275 --> 10:52.687
Sorry.

11:12.589 --> 11:15.922
Anita, do you ever get scared?

11:19.053 --> 11:22.295
I think everyone does.

11:31.274 --> 11:34.641
[Music playing,
indistinct conversations]

11:43.745 --> 11:44.734
Okay, ground rules.

11:44.871 --> 11:47.408
If you drink too much,
I'm not carrying you home.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.531
Don't do drugs in front of me.

11:49.667 --> 11:51.749
I don't want to talk to
any of your little friends,

11:51.878 --> 11:53.960
and don't try and have sex
with any of my friends.

11:54.088 --> 11:55.043
Anything else?

11:55.173 --> 11:57.334
No, that's it.
Try and enjoy yourself.

11:57.467 --> 11:58.923
Yeah, like that's gonna happen.

11:59.052 --> 12:00.167
Toby!

12:00.303 --> 12:02.544
Hey, Caroline.

12:02.680 --> 12:04.386
No one knew
if you were coming or not.

12:04.515 --> 12:05.379
Do you want a drink?

12:05.516 --> 12:06.722
I've got some ciders hidden
in the washing machine.

12:06.851 --> 12:08.807
Of course he does.

12:09.520 --> 12:12.387
Yeah, yeah.
That would be nice.

12:16.986 --> 12:19.238
-Girl in my class.
-All right, Casanova.

12:19.364 --> 12:22.401
Enjoy your spin-cycle ciders.

12:29.540 --> 12:34.660
Anita, you've got access
to Laura's desktop, haven't you?

12:34.796 --> 12:40.166
Can you check
her e-mails, calendar, phone?

12:40.301 --> 12:42.633
I am not able to access
personal information

12:42.762 --> 12:44.548
unless requested to
by the owner.

12:44.681 --> 12:46.592
JOE:
All right, well, the car's got

12:46.724 --> 12:49.511
one of those anti-theft
tracking devices, right?

12:49.644 --> 12:51.635
You can tap into that,
can't you?

12:51.771 --> 12:52.931
Find its location?

12:55.024 --> 12:56.730
It's my car, Anita.

12:56.859 --> 12:59.566
I want you to track it, please.

13:00.947 --> 13:03.984
The car is currently
driving north on Brook Street.

13:06.452 --> 13:07.828
It's noisy in here.

13:07.954 --> 13:10.570
Do you want to go outside
and talk?

13:10.707 --> 13:11.617
I can hear okay.

13:11.749 --> 13:15.162
CAROLINE: I mean,
do you want to go somewhere?

13:15.295 --> 13:16.580
Just you and me.

13:16.671 --> 13:19.629
Just you and me?

13:24.762 --> 13:27.253
Um, I-I do.

13:27.390 --> 13:31.008
Really -- Really do.

13:31.144 --> 13:32.680
But...

13:32.812 --> 13:34.427
Butlcant

13:34.564 --> 13:36.555
Of course you can.

13:36.691 --> 13:38.147
No,|cant

13:38.276 --> 13:40.608
There's...

13:40.737 --> 13:43.524
There's someone else.

13:43.656 --> 13:45.863
I think I like someone else.

13:48.494 --> 13:50.359
Your loss.

13:52.582 --> 13:54.493
Yeah.

13:56.419 --> 13:58.080
[Wine pouring]

13:58.212 --> 14:00.954
Where is it now?

14:01.090 --> 14:02.250
Edmund Street.

14:02.383 --> 14:05.921
It's been there for
three minutes and 28 seconds.

14:06.054 --> 14:08.887
Right, so she's parked.

14:09.015 --> 14:12.223
Where exactly is she?

14:12.352 --> 14:14.843
What house number?

14:14.979 --> 14:17.220
I don't have that information.

14:17.357 --> 14:19.268
Okay.

14:19.400 --> 14:25.236
Run a cross-check on
Laura's work and Edmund Street,

14:25.365 --> 14:27.856
see if anyone she works with
is living there.

14:27.992 --> 14:31.075
I can find no record
of anyone at Laura's firm

14:31.204 --> 14:34.116
living on Edmund Street.

14:34.248 --> 14:38.082
Is there anyone called Tom
living there?

14:39.253 --> 14:41.460
ANITA: There are three residents
on Edmund Street

14:41.589 --> 14:43.830
with the first name Thomas.

14:48.137 --> 14:49.843
I'm going over there.

14:52.392 --> 14:54.678
Don't do that, Joe.

14:58.356 --> 15:00.722
You don't know how this feels.

15:00.858 --> 15:03.474
How could you?
You can't feel.

15:03.611 --> 15:05.977
You got no idea.

15:09.242 --> 15:12.200
At 5:22 pm,
Laura dialed the landline

15:12.328 --> 15:14.239
to a Mrs. Alexandra Kennedy

15:14.372 --> 15:16.078
and confirmed a meeting
at her house this evening

15:16.207 --> 15:19.370
regarding her lawsuit.

15:21.921 --> 15:23.457
Thank you.

15:23.589 --> 15:25.250
I was surprised to hear
from you.

15:25.383 --> 15:27.544
Your firm told me
that I didn't have a case.

15:27.677 --> 15:29.167
Right, yes.
They did. We did.

15:29.303 --> 15:32.295
I just wanted to do a follow-up,
if that's okay.

15:32.432 --> 15:33.342
Oh, of course.

15:33.474 --> 15:35.965
I wanted to ask you both
some questions

15:36.102 --> 15:38.218
about what happened
at the theater.

15:38.354 --> 15:40.845
Well, we settled down
to watch the play.

15:40.982 --> 15:43.564
20 minutes in, an usher
comes along and tells me

15:43.693 --> 15:46.025
that I need to take Howard out.

15:46.154 --> 15:48.896
No synths allowed.

15:49.031 --> 15:52.819
But Howard's not just
some synth.

15:52.952 --> 15:54.943
In what way?

15:55.079 --> 15:57.456
He understands
what he's watching.

16:00.042 --> 16:02.419
Is it true, Howard?

16:02.545 --> 16:05.252
When you watch the plays,
what do you feel?

16:05.381 --> 16:06.496
HOWARD:
It depends.

16:06.632 --> 16:09.499
Sometimes plays
are supposed to make you laugh.

16:09.635 --> 16:12.297
Sometimes they're supposed to
make you cry.

16:12.430 --> 16:13.886
All plays are different.

16:14.015 --> 16:16.927
LAURA:
This play, then.

16:17.059 --> 16:20.517
How did it affect you
before you were thrown out?

16:20.646 --> 16:23.103
The story begins
when Willy Loman,

16:23.232 --> 16:24.563
a traveling salesman,

16:24.692 --> 16:28.150
returns to his family home
in Brooklyn, New York City.

16:28.279 --> 16:30.110
-His wife gets up to meet him.
-That's the plot, Howard.

16:30.239 --> 16:31.649
She --

16:31.782 --> 16:33.522
What did you feel?

16:50.301 --> 16:53.213
Sometimes wish my family came
with instructions.

16:55.806 --> 16:58.764
Or me.

17:08.986 --> 17:11.773
Can you feel awkwardness?

17:13.824 --> 17:15.689
Just as well.

17:17.828 --> 17:22.162
Wonder what it's like,
not feeling anything.

17:22.291 --> 17:26.250
It's got to drag, after a while,
hasn't it?

17:27.213 --> 17:29.795
I mean, what about this?

17:29.924 --> 17:31.915
This unlocks you,

17:32.051 --> 17:35.134
makes you...passionate.

17:35.263 --> 17:36.969
That's a feeling.

17:37.098 --> 17:39.555
It creates
the impression of passion.

17:39.684 --> 17:41.640
It's a simulation of an emotion.

17:41.769 --> 17:43.976
Yeah, but it's one of
the good ones,

17:44.105 --> 17:47.268
as far as I can remember.

17:48.859 --> 17:50.565
Do you want to try it?

17:50.695 --> 17:52.811
Just out of curiosity.

17:53.698 --> 17:57.532
I mean, we won't do anything,
obviously.

17:57.660 --> 17:59.901
Alex, he doesn't have
any human rights.

18:00.037 --> 18:00.822
You know that.

18:00.955 --> 18:05.198
Howard doesn't enjoy the play
any more than your wristwatch.

18:05.334 --> 18:07.711
He's just better
at convincing you.

18:07.837 --> 18:09.418
I'm not a madwoman.

18:09.547 --> 18:12.459
I don't believe
that Howard is a human.

18:12.592 --> 18:15.755
But I also don't believe
that he is an inanimate object

18:15.886 --> 18:18.969
